    .entry-details
      %p.desc
        %strong> Description:
        Convert an array-like object into a true JavaScript array.
      %ul.signatures
        %li.signature{:id => "jQuery.makeArray-obj"}
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.2/"} 1.2
            jQuery.makeArray( obj )
          %p.arguement
            %strong> obj
            Any object to turn into a native Array.
      .longdesc
        %p
          Many methods, both in jQuery and in JavaScript in general, return objects that are array-like. For example, the jQuery factory function
          %code $()
          returns a jQuery object that has many of the properties of an array (a length, the
          %code []
          array access operator, etc.), but is not exactly the same as an array and lacks some of an array's built-in methods (such as
          %code .pop()
          and
          = succeed ")." do
            %code .reverse()
        %p Note that after the conversion, any special features the object had (such as the jQuery methods in our example) will no longer be present. The object is now a plain array.
      %h3 Examples:
      #entry-examples.entry-examples
        #example-0
          %h4
            Example:
            %span.desc Turn a collection of HTMLElements into an Array of them.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;style&gt;
                  div { color:red; }
                  &lt;/style&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	&lt;div&gt;First&lt;/div&gt;
                  &lt;div&gt;Second&lt;/div&gt;  
                  &lt;div&gt;Third&lt;/div&gt;
                
                  &lt;div&gt;Fourth&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;script&gt;
                    var elems = document.getElementsByTagName("div"); // returns a nodeList
                    var arr = jQuery.makeArray(elems);
                    arr.reverse(); // use an Array method on list of dom elements
                    $(arr).appendTo(document.body);
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
          .demo.code-demo
